title: Linked List Cycle II
content: Given a linked list, return the node where the cycle begins. If there is no cycle, return . There is a cycle in a linked list if there is some node in the list that can be reached again by continuously following the pointer. Internally, is used to denote the index of the node that tail's pointer is connected to. Note that is not passed as a parameter. Notice that you should not modify the linked list. The number of the nodes in the list is in the range . is or a valid index in the linked-list.
